---
import RootLayout from "@/layouts/root-layout.astro";
---

<RootLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Clipwise AI Chrome Extension"
>
  <main id="main-content" class="py-12">
    <article class="mx-auto max-w-4xl space-y-8 px-4">
      <header class="space-y-2">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="font-semibold">Clipwise AI</p>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          <time datetime="2026-01-06">Last updated: January 6, 2026</time>
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Overview</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Clipwise AI is a browser extension that converts webpages to Markdown
          format. Your privacy is important to us, and this policy explains how
          the extension handles your data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Data Controller</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          The data controller for Clipwise AI is Dennis Morello, an independent
          software developer based in Italy. For any privacy-related inquiries,
          you can contact the data controller at
          <a
            href="mailto:dennismorello@gmail.com"
            class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
            >dennismorello@gmail.com</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Data Collection</h2>
        <p class="font-semibold">
          Clipwise AI does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data or
          webpage content to our servers.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          The extension only accesses webpage content after an explicit user
          action (clicking the extension icon). All webpage content processing
          happens entirely within your browser. We have no ability to access,
          view, or store any content you convert. External communication only
          occurs for premium license validation and when you explicitly use the
          "Open in ChatGPT/Claude" feature.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Under the
          <a
            href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/reg/2016/679/oj"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
            >General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)</a
          >
          and other applicable privacy laws, we process limited data based on the
          following legal grounds:
        </p>
        <dl class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold">
              Contractual necessity (<a
                href="https://gdpr-info.eu/art-6-gdpr/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
                >Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR</a
              >)
            </dt>
            <dd class="text-muted-foreground">
              For premium license holders, we process license keys and browser
              instance identifiers to fulfill our contractual obligation to
              provide you with the premium features you purchased.
            </dd>
          </div>

          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold">
              Legitimate interest (<a
                href="https://gdpr-info.eu/art-6-gdpr/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
                >Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR</a
              >)
            </dt>
            <dd class="text-muted-foreground">
              We have a legitimate interest in preventing fraud and enforcing
              license activation limits (up to 3 browsers per license) to
              protect our business and ensure fair use of the service.
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          For free tier users, no personal data is processed externally—all
          operations occur locally in your browser without any legal basis
          requirement.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">How the Extension Works</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          When you click the Clipwise AI extension icon:
        </p>
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-2 pl-6 text-muted-foreground">
          <li>The extension reads the HTML content of the current webpage</li>
          <li>
            Content is processed locally using Mozilla Readability to extract
            the main article
          </li>
          <li>
            The extracted content is converted to Markdown format using Turndown
          </li>
          <li>
            The result is stored temporarily in your browser's local storage
          </li>
          <li>
            Your daily conversion count is tracked locally to enforce free tier
            limits (resets at midnight)
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Permissions Explained</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Clipwise AI requests the following permissions:
        </p>
        <dl class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold">activeTab</dt>
            <dd class="text-muted-foreground">
              Allows the extension to read the current page's content only when
              you click the extension icon. The extension cannot access any page
              without your explicit action.
            </dd>
          </div>

          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold">storage</dt>
            <dd class="text-muted-foreground">
              Used to store the converted Markdown, your daily conversion count,
              and premium license data (if applicable) in your browser's local
              storage. All data stays on your device.
            </dd>
          </div>

          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold">sidePanel</dt>
            <dd class="text-muted-foreground">
              Enables the extension to display the converted Markdown in
              Chrome's built-in side panel interface.
            </dd>
          </div>

          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold">scripting</dt>
            <dd class="text-muted-foreground">
              Required to inject a small script that reads the page's HTML
              content when you click the extension icon. Also used for the "Open
              in ChatGPT/Claude" feature to automatically fill the prompt input.
            </dd>
          </div>

          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold">tabs</dt>
            <dd class="text-muted-foreground">
              Used only for the "Open in ChatGPT/Claude" feature to create a new
              tab and detect when the AI service page has finished loading.
            </dd>
          </div>

          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold">
              Host permissions (chatgpt.com, claude.ai)
            </dt>
            <dd class="text-muted-foreground">
              Required only for the "Open in ChatGPT/Claude" feature. Allows the
              extension to automatically paste your converted Markdown into the
              AI prompt input. These permissions are never used unless you
              explicitly click the corresponding button.
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Open in ChatGPT/Claude Feature</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Clipwise AI includes an optional feature to send your converted
          Markdown directly to ChatGPT or Claude. This feature is entirely
          user-initiated—the extension will never send your content to these
          services automatically.
        </p>
        <p class="font-semibold">When you use this feature:</p>
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-2 pl-6 text-muted-foreground">
          <li>
            The extension opens a new browser tab with the selected AI service
            (chatgpt.com or claude.ai)
          </li>
          <li>
            Once the page loads, the extension automatically pastes your
            converted Markdown into the prompt input
          </li>
          <li>
            Your content is then subject to the AI service's privacy policy
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="font-semibold">Important:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-muted-foreground">
          <li>
            This is an optional feature—you can always use the "Copy" button
            instead
          </li>
          <li>
            The content goes directly to the AI service; Clipwise AI does not
            intercept, store, or process it
          </li>
          <li>
            Review the privacy policies of
            <a
              href="https://openai.com/policies/privacy-policy"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
              >OpenAI (ChatGPT)</a
            >
            and
            <a
              href="https://www.anthropic.com/legal/privacy"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
              >Anthropic (Claude)</a
            >
            to understand how they handle your data
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Premium License Validation</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          If you purchase a premium license, the extension communicates with
          Lemon Squeezy (our payment and licensing provider) to validate your
          license. This is the only external network communication the extension
          makes.
        </p>
        <p class="font-semibold">What data is sent to Lemon Squeezy:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-muted-foreground">
          <li>Your license key (to verify it's valid and active)</li>
          <li>
            A unique browser instance identifier (to enforce device limits—up to
            3 browsers per license)
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="font-semibold">What is NOT sent:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-muted-foreground">
          <li>Any webpage content you convert</li>
          <li>Your browsing history or URLs</li>
          <li>Any other personal information</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          License validation occurs when you activate a license and periodically
          (once per day) while using premium features. If you use only the free
          tier, no external network requests are made.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Data Sharing</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          We do not share your webpage content or browsing data with any third
          parties. For premium users, only license validation data (license key
          and browser instance ID) is shared with Lemon Squeezy to verify your
          subscription.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Clipwise AI may interact with the following third-party services:
        </p>
        <dl class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold">Lemon Squeezy (Payment & Licensing)</dt>
            <dd class="space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
              <p>
                Lemon Squeezy acts as an independent data controller for payment
                processing, invoicing, VAT handling, and transactional emails.
                When you purchase a premium license, Lemon Squeezy collects and
                processes your payment information, billing address, and email
                address according to their own privacy policy.
              </p>
              <p>
                For license validation, Lemon Squeezy acts as a data processor
                on our behalf, processing only your license key and browser
                instance identifier to verify your subscription status.
              </p>
              <p>
                See
                <a
                  href="https://www.lemonsqueezy.com/privacy"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
                  >Lemon Squeezy's Privacy Policy</a
                >
                for their complete data handling practices.
              </p>
            </dd>
          </div>

          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold">OpenAI (ChatGPT)</dt>
            <dd class="text-muted-foreground">
              Only accessed if you use the "Open in ChatGPT" feature. Your
              converted Markdown is sent directly to their service. See
              <a
                href="https://openai.com/policies/privacy-policy"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
                >OpenAI's Privacy Policy</a
              >.
            </dd>
          </div>

          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold">Anthropic (Claude)</dt>
            <dd class="text-muted-foreground">
              Only accessed if you use the "Open in Claude" feature. Your
              converted Markdown is sent directly to their service. See
              <a
                href="https://www.anthropic.com/legal/privacy"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
                >Anthropic's Privacy Policy</a
              >.
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          We do not use any analytics platforms or tracking systems.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Data Security</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Since all processing occurs locally within your browser and no data is
          transmitted externally, your content remains secure on your device.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Data Retention</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          We retain data according to the following criteria:
        </p>
        <dl class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold">Local browser storage</dt>
            <dd class="text-muted-foreground">
              Converted Markdown content and daily conversion counts are stored
              temporarily in your browser's local storage. This data is cleared
              when you clear your browser data or uninstall the extension.
              Conversion counts reset automatically at midnight each day.
            </dd>
          </div>

          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold">Premium license data</dt>
            <dd class="text-muted-foreground">
              License keys and browser instance identifiers are stored locally
              for as long as your license remains active. When you deactivate
              your license or it expires, this data is removed from your
              browser. Lemon Squeezy retains purchase records according to their
              own retention policy and applicable tax regulations.
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Your Rights</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Under
          <a
            href="https://gdpr-info.eu/chapter-3/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
            >Chapter 3 of the GDPR</a
          >
          and other applicable privacy laws, you have the following rights regarding
          your personal data:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-muted-foreground">
          <li>
            <strong>Right of access</strong> (<a
              href="https://gdpr-info.eu/art-15-gdpr/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80">Art. 15</a
            >): You can request information about what personal data we hold
            about you.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to rectification</strong> (<a
              href="https://gdpr-info.eu/art-16-gdpr/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80">Art. 16</a
            >): You can request correction of inaccurate personal data.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to erasure</strong> (<a
              href="https://gdpr-info.eu/art-17-gdpr/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80">Art. 17</a
            >): You can request deletion of your personal data. For local data,
            you can clear it yourself through your browser settings. For
            license-related data held by Lemon Squeezy, contact them directly or
            reach out to us for assistance.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to restriction</strong> (<a
              href="https://gdpr-info.eu/art-18-gdpr/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80">Art. 18</a
            >): You can request that we limit how we use your data.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to data portability</strong> (<a
              href="https://gdpr-info.eu/art-20-gdpr/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80">Art. 20</a
            >): You can request a copy of your data in a machine-readable
            format.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to object</strong> (<a
              href="https://gdpr-info.eu/art-21-gdpr/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80">Art. 21</a
            >): You can object to processing based on legitimate interests.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to lodge a complaint</strong> (<a
              href="https://gdpr-info.eu/art-77-gdpr/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80">Art. 77</a
            >): You have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection
            supervisory authority. For users in Italy, this is the
            <a
              href="https://www.garanteprivacy.it"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
              lang="it"><em>Garante per la protezione dei dati personali</em></a
            >
            (Italian Data Protection Authority). Users in other EU/EEA countries can
            find their local supervisory authority on the
            <a
              href="https://edpb.europa.eu/about-edpb/about-edpb/members_en"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
              >European Data Protection Board (EDPB) website</a
            >.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at
          <a
            href="mailto:dennismorello@gmail.com"
            class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
            >dennismorello@gmail.com</a
          >. We will respond to your request within 30 days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Clipwise AI is available worldwide. While all webpage content
          processing occurs locally in your browser, premium license validation
          may involve data transfers to Lemon Squeezy's servers, which may be
          located outside your country of residence.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          For users in the European Economic Area (EEA), United Kingdom, or
          Switzerland, any transfer of personal data outside these regions is
          conducted in compliance with applicable data protection laws, relying
          on appropriate safeguards such as Standard Contractual Clauses or
          adequacy decisions where applicable. Lemon Squeezy's data protection
          practices can be reviewed in their
          <a
            href="https://www.lemonsqueezy.com/privacy"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
            >Privacy Policy</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          Clipwise AI does not knowingly collect any personal data from children
          under the age of 16. If you believe a child has provided us with
          personal data, please contact us and we will take steps to delete such
          information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will
          be reflected in the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          If you have questions about this privacy policy, please contact us at
          <a
            href="mailto:dennismorello@gmail.com"
            class="text-primary underline hover:text-primary/80"
            >dennismorello@gmail.com</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>

      <aside class="border-t pt-6">
        <p class="text-sm italic text-muted-foreground">
          This privacy policy applies to the Clipwise AI Chrome extension.
        </p>
      </aside>
    </article>
  </main>
</RootLayout>
